wikipedia_page.main: Mike Hogan (born 9 May 1943) is a British hurdler. He competed in the men's 400 metres hurdles at the 1964 Summer Olympics.

link_mentions.page: Athletics at the 1964 Summer Olympics – Men's 400 metres hurdles

response: He competed in the men's 400 metres hurdles at the 1964 Summer Olympics. Warden, Mike Hogan and the eventual silver medalist John Cooper were the only two British men to contest the event. Warden progressed to the semi-final after placing third in his heat with a time of 51.6 seconds. He unfortunately missed out on a place in the Olympic final by just two hundredths of a second after placing fifth in his semi-final behind the gold medalist Rex Cawley.
